St Paul’s School Canteen Pre-Order System  
By Ray Qiu — Class 10R  
Teacher: Mr Fenwick  
Sprint 4 Final Project Submission


##Project Overview
This project is a fully functional **canteen pre-order system** for St Paul's School.  
It allows students to browse the menu and place food orders, while kitchen staff can manage menu items, update order statuses, and export order data.

The system is built using:
- **Python**
- **Flask**
- **SQLite**
- **HTML + CSS**
- **Jinja2 Templates**

Features

Student Features
- Register new account  
- Login securely  
- View daily menu  
- See item images and prices  
- Add items to cart / place orders  
- View all past and current orders  
- Track order status (Pending → Ready → Completed)

---

Kitchen Features
- Login as kitchen staff  
- Add new menu items  
- Upload food images  
- Toggle availability of items  
- View all orders from students  
- Update order status  
- Export all orders to CSV  

Database Models (SQLite)

**User**
| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| id | Integer | Primary Key |
| username | Text | Unique |
| password | Text | For login (plain for demo only) |
| role | Text | 'student' or 'kitchen' |

**MenuItem**
| Field | Type |
|-------|------|
| id | Integer |
| name | Text |
| price | Float |
| image | Text |
| available | Boolean |

**Order**
| Field | Type |
|-------|------|
| id | Integer |
| student_id | Integer |
| item_id | Integer |
| quantity | Integer |
| price_at_time | Float |
| status | Text |

How to Run the Project (Important)

Install required modules

